---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Pagination from "../../components/Pagination.astro";
import Picture from "../../components/Picture.astro";
import BrowserFrame from "../../components/BrowserFrame.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="GTreasury" pathname="/work/gtreasury/" caseStudy={true}>
  <div class="case-study">
    <div class="case-study-header">
      <div class="case-study-header-content constrain">
        <h1>GTreasury</h1>
        <div class="case-study-header-nav">
          <a title="Previous" href="/work/material-palettes/"
            ><Pagination name="previous" /></a
          >
          <a title="Next" href="/work/balto/"><Pagination name="next" /></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-overview">
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>My role:</strong> UX engineer
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The problem:</strong> Core financial workflows were fragmented across
          six codebases, a dozen color palettes, and aging legacy frameworks, while
          years of acquisitions and shifting priorities produced conflicting interactions
          across the platform, increasing errors and making basic tasks tedious to
          learn and complete.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Top outcome:</strong> Developed and deployed the <em
            >Obelisk</em
          > design system, a centralized component library that unified five product
          lines and accelerated modernization efforts.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-content">
      <h2>Context and scope</h2>
      <p>
        GTreasury builds enterprise treasury management software used by global
        corporations to manage cash, liquidity, debt, payments, and financial
        risk. The core application is a legacy web system with decades of
        incremental development, resulting in fragmented and inconsistent
        experiences over time.
      </p>
      <p>
        Working alongside a UX specialist responsible for user research, I
        focused on translating findings into system-level design decisions
        through early-stage exploration, rapid prototyping, and iterative
        validation with users.
      </p>
      <h2>Execution</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Systemic audit and redesign:</strong> Examined disconnected codebases
          to identify shared interface patterns and formalize a unified design system,
          producing structured, reusable artifacts to support modernization.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Priority prototyping:</strong> Reimagined critical workflows (e.g.,
          payment creation and cash worksheet management) based on user interview
          insights, validating improvements through high-fidelity prototypes leveraging
          the design system.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Implementation:</strong> Partnered with a frontend engineer to build
          a <a href="https://gtreasury.netlify.app/">coded prototype</a> with Angular
          and Kendo UI, ensuring layout precision and proper handling of interactive
          states. Later, extended these patterns into production CSS, adapting for
          real-world constraints and existing dependencies.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-visuals pswp-gallery">
      <BrowserFrame
        title="gtreasury.netlify.app"
        url="https://gtreasury.netlify.app/financial-instruments/portfolios"
      />
      <Picture name="gt-brainstorm" alt="Brainstorming sticky notes" lightbox />
      <Picture
        name="gt-palette"
        alt="Design system shot, color palette"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="gt-buttons"
        alt="Design system shot, button component"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="gt-wizard"
        alt="Design system shot, wizard component"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="gt-table"
        alt="Design system shot, table functions"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="gt-dashboard-flow"
        alt="High-fidelity dashboard"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="gt-dashboard-create"
        alt="Product shot, create dashboard"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture name="gt-dashboard" alt="Product shot, dashboard" lightbox />
      <Picture name="gt-form" alt="Product shot, create deal" lightbox />
      <Picture name="gt-worksheet" alt="Product shot, worksheet" lightbox />
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
